act.article:
2 Definitions.—In these rules, unless the context otherwise requires,—
a ‘cattle’ means oxen, buffaloes, cows, bullocks and horses, including their young ones;
b ‘certificate’ means the certificate of Registration;
c ‘registering authority’ means such officers of the veterinary department of the State Government or of a local authority as the State Government may, by general or special order, specify in this behalf.
